WEBVTT

00:06.297 --> 00:11.928
- ♪ I hear you whispering... ♪

00:12.011 --> 00:16.725
♪ But nobody's there ♪

00:16.808 --> 00:17.976
[dramatic note]

00:18.059 --> 00:22.439
♪ My eyes are still looking ♪

00:22.522 --> 00:23.690
- [grunts]

00:23.773 --> 00:24.899
- [gasps]

00:24.983 --> 00:26.776
[tense music]

00:26.860 --> 00:28.570
[keypad beeps]

00:29.320 --> 00:31.990
- [grunting distantly]

00:32.073 --> 00:37.996
♪ ♪

00:38.079 --> 00:39.247
[grunts]
- I'm sorry.

00:39.330 --> 00:41.833
- Thomas, don't do this.

00:41.916 --> 00:46.087
♪ ♪

00:46.171 --> 00:47.964
See you in hell.

00:48.047 --> 00:50.884
- [breathing heavily]

00:50.967 --> 00:55.013
♪ ♪

00:55.096 --> 00:56.347
- Drop the gun.

00:56.431 --> 00:58.016
- It's okay, Martha--
- Don't move.

00:59.350 --> 01:01.102
- I was just turning around--

01:01.186 --> 01:03.563
- Put the gun down first,
Thomas.

01:03.646 --> 01:06.566
- I mean it.

01:06.649 --> 01:08.193
Put it down, now.

01:08.276 --> 01:10.111
- Jesus, Martha, relax.

01:13.698 --> 01:16.451
- What the fuck are you doing?

01:16.534 --> 01:18.495
- I had a bad dream.

01:18.578 --> 01:20.246
- Okay.

01:21.039 --> 01:25.627
Well, next time,
wake me up and let me know.

01:25.710 --> 01:27.754
Because I nearly shot you,
Thomas.

01:31.549 --> 01:34.052
It's a great marriage
we got going, huh?

01:35.011 --> 01:36.805
- Yeah.

01:36.888 --> 01:40.141
We have to find a way
past this.

01:40.225 --> 01:41.851
It's been a month.

01:41.935 --> 01:44.479
- Any ideas?

01:44.562 --> 01:47.148
- Well...

01:47.232 --> 01:49.359
you can stop acting
like you're scared of me.

01:49.442 --> 01:50.735
- I'm not acting scared of you.

01:50.819 --> 01:52.153
I am scared of you.

01:53.112 --> 01:55.031
- Well, all I can do

01:55.114 --> 01:57.283
is keep telling you
that I'm sorry

01:57.367 --> 02:00.453
and that I will never,
ever, hurt you again.

02:00.537 --> 02:02.997
It wasn't me who attacked you.

02:03.081 --> 02:04.958
It wasn't me.
- I know.

02:06.000 --> 02:08.711
But it was you that chose
your father over me.

02:08.795 --> 02:12.382
At least that's how it feels.
- I didn't!

02:12.465 --> 02:13.675
I made a mistake.

02:13.758 --> 02:15.510
He's my father.
I trusted him.

02:15.593 --> 02:18.429
And you lied to me.
- Oh, my God, here we go again.

02:18.513 --> 02:20.014
- Yes, here we go again,
because it was those lies

02:20.098 --> 02:22.308
that started this--
- No, enough, Thomas!

02:22.392 --> 02:24.227
[dramatic music]

02:24.310 --> 02:26.521
Need to go to sleep.

02:26.604 --> 02:28.690
♪ ♪

02:28.773 --> 02:30.650
- Martha, I'm sorry.
I...

02:33.111 --> 02:35.155
- Yeah.

02:35.238 --> 02:36.698
Me too.

02:36.781 --> 02:38.741
Make sure you put
that gun away.

02:38.825 --> 02:45.206
♪ ♪

02:45.290 --> 02:48.251
[adventurous music]

02:48.334 --> 02:55.425
♪ ♪

03:46.476 --> 03:48.978
- Where are you off to,
looking like that?

03:49.062 --> 03:50.438
- What's wrong
with the way I look?

03:50.521 --> 03:52.398
- Nothing,
you look nice, is all.

03:52.482 --> 03:54.400
- Then just say that.

03:54.484 --> 03:56.903
I'm meeting someone.
- Who?

03:56.986 --> 03:58.655
- Do I ask who you're meeting
every time

03:58.738 --> 04:00.031
you walk out the door?

04:00.114 --> 04:01.574
- As a matter of fact,
you do, yeah.

04:01.658 --> 04:03.618
- And you rarely tell me,

04:03.701 --> 04:06.913
which is probably a blessing,
truth be told.

04:06.996 --> 04:08.373
If you must know,

04:08.456 --> 04:09.540
I'm meeting Roger,

04:09.624 --> 04:10.917
and I don't want
to hear about it.

04:12.377 --> 04:14.462
- That bloke who legged it
out of here last month?

04:14.545 --> 04:16.464
- He did no such thing.
- Like a rabbit.

04:16.547 --> 04:17.924
- Can you blame him if he did?

04:18.007 --> 04:19.467
Most people aren't used
to your shenanigans.

04:19.550 --> 04:20.969
- Well,
he just didn't seem to have

04:21.052 --> 04:22.762
much of a constitution,
is all I'm saying.

04:22.845 --> 04:24.847
And you have to admit, it's
pretty poor form he made you

04:24.931 --> 04:26.641
wait so long
before ringing you again.

04:26.724 --> 04:29.936
- He didn't ring me.
I rang him.

04:30.019 --> 04:31.104
- You rang him?

04:31.187 --> 04:32.480
- And why not?

04:32.563 --> 04:34.148
Times are changing.

04:34.232 --> 04:35.400
A woman can ring a man

04:35.483 --> 04:37.151
without the world
coming to an end.

04:37.235 --> 04:39.529
- I was only asking.

04:39.612 --> 04:42.865
And you can see
who you like, obviously.

04:42.949 --> 04:45.702
- Well, thank you very much.

04:45.785 --> 04:49.205
By the way, while you
were having a nice long kip,

04:49.288 --> 04:51.332
the Prime Minister's Office
called.

04:51.416 --> 04:53.418
They want to see you
as soon as possible.

04:53.501 --> 04:55.086
- Really?
He say what about?

04:55.169 --> 04:57.880
- No, and I didn't ask.
- Why not?

04:57.964 --> 05:00.258
- Because I'm not
you're bleedin' secretary.

05:00.341 --> 05:01.801
- Mm.

05:01.884 --> 05:03.594
- Is everything all right?

05:03.678 --> 05:06.764
You're not mixed up
with anything, are you?

05:06.848 --> 05:08.391
- Not that I know of.

05:08.474 --> 05:10.476
Business has been
a bit slow as of late.

05:10.560 --> 05:12.395
Would be nice if he was
calling about a job.

05:12.478 --> 05:13.896
- Oh.

05:13.980 --> 05:16.024
I'm sure it
will work itself out.

05:18.568 --> 05:20.486
I'm off.

05:20.570 --> 05:22.238
There's bread
for toast if you're hungry.

05:22.322 --> 05:23.781
- Mum.

05:25.158 --> 05:27.118
You look lovely.

05:28.661 --> 05:30.038
- Thank you, Alfie.

05:32.707 --> 05:34.292
- Hm.

05:34.375 --> 05:37.336
[slow dramatic music]

05:37.420 --> 05:43.634
♪ ♪

05:43.718 --> 05:44.886
- Good afternoon, young lady.

05:44.969 --> 05:46.471
What seems to be the problem?

05:46.554 --> 05:48.514
- Oh, no problem.

05:49.891 --> 05:51.976
- Hello, Mrs. G.

05:52.060 --> 05:53.895
- Well, I'll be damned.

05:53.978 --> 05:55.646
Mai Lin, thank you.

05:58.441 --> 06:00.276
Come, come.

06:04.739 --> 06:05.865
[shuts door]

06:05.948 --> 06:08.284
Well, Bet Sykes.

06:08.367 --> 06:09.911
How are you, my dear?

06:09.994 --> 06:12.163
- Well enough.
You?

06:12.246 --> 06:14.207
- Oh, I'm in fine fettle.

06:14.290 --> 06:16.751
I rather thought
you'd be dead by now,

06:16.834 --> 06:18.419
given the way
that you carry on.

06:18.503 --> 06:19.712
- Never better, me.

06:19.796 --> 06:21.255
- I heard
about the former Ravens

06:21.339 --> 06:23.382
being murdered.
That was you, I suppose.

06:23.466 --> 06:25.843
- Murdered? No.

06:25.927 --> 06:28.596
Put down, I call it.
[snickers]

06:28.679 --> 06:30.556
- Well, how on Earth
did you track them down?

06:30.640 --> 06:32.433
Well, how did you track me
down, for that matter?

06:32.517 --> 06:35.061
- A little something
I took from Miss Vixen.

06:39.065 --> 06:40.691
- I see.

06:41.984 --> 06:44.779
And this is her baby,
is it?

06:44.862 --> 06:46.072
- Julie.

06:46.155 --> 06:47.281
Sweet, isn't she?

06:47.365 --> 06:48.783
- Yes, she is.

06:48.866 --> 06:51.410
Oh, Bet. Really?

06:51.494 --> 06:54.956
- Never you mind her.
We've business to discuss.

06:55.039 --> 06:56.666
- I can't possibly see
what business

06:56.749 --> 06:58.501
we might have at this point.

06:58.584 --> 07:02.255
- John Salt, of course.
I need to know where he is.

07:02.338 --> 07:04.215
- I'm afraid
I can't tell you that.

07:04.298 --> 07:07.135
- Can't or won't?

07:07.218 --> 07:09.303
- Won't, to be more precise.

07:09.387 --> 07:12.306
I know where he is,
and I won't tell you.

07:12.390 --> 07:15.393
- You'll tell us,
or I'll shoot you.

07:15.476 --> 07:18.771
Don't think I won't.
- I do think you won't.

07:18.855 --> 07:21.524
- How's that, then?
- You're not a monster, Bet.

07:21.607 --> 07:23.484
You're just
a misguided young woman,

07:23.568 --> 07:24.944
but not a monster.

07:25.027 --> 07:28.114
Now, would you like
a cup of tea?

07:28.197 --> 07:29.866
- Go on, then.

07:29.949 --> 07:33.161
Proper tea, mind.
None of that Earl Grey rubbish.

07:33.244 --> 07:34.829
- All right.

07:36.581 --> 07:39.584
[dramatic percussion music]

07:39.667 --> 07:41.419
♪ ♪

07:48.843 --> 07:50.428
- Ah, Mr. Prime Minister.

07:50.511 --> 07:52.221
- Alfred.
- Busy around here.

07:52.305 --> 07:55.474
- The summit starts next week,
but Commonwealth leaders

07:55.558 --> 07:58.394
have already begun to arrive,
so I'm quite pressed for time.

07:58.477 --> 08:00.521
- Well, I've got
quite a busy schedule myself,

08:00.605 --> 08:02.190
but I was glad you called.

08:02.273 --> 08:03.733
Thought you might still be
cross with me

08:03.816 --> 08:05.443
for breaking Thomas Wayne
out of the Tower.

08:05.526 --> 08:07.278
Not that I'm saying I did.

08:07.361 --> 08:08.779
Papers say
all sorts, don't they?

08:08.863 --> 08:10.406
- I should have you arrested.

08:10.489 --> 08:12.241
No doubt you'll be back
behind bars at some point,

08:12.325 --> 08:14.535
but until then,
your services can be useful.

08:14.619 --> 08:15.953
- Fair play.

08:16.037 --> 08:17.872
What kind of services
did you have in mind?

08:17.955 --> 08:20.583
- What do you know about
the island nation of Kalpoor?

08:20.666 --> 08:21.959
- Not much.

08:22.043 --> 08:23.836
Used to be a colony of ours,
didn't it?

08:23.920 --> 08:25.171
- Yeah.
Well, after gaining

08:25.254 --> 08:26.756
their independence
ten years ago,

08:26.839 --> 08:28.382
their government has faced
intense opposition

08:28.466 --> 08:29.926
from a radical separatist group

08:30.009 --> 08:31.719
known as
the Kalpoor Freedom Party,

08:31.802 --> 08:33.054
which controls
several districts

08:33.137 --> 08:34.805
in the southern end
of the island.

08:34.889 --> 08:37.934
They're led by
a woman named Zahra Khin,

08:38.017 --> 08:39.852
who arrived
in London yesterday.

08:39.936 --> 08:41.145
- She's here for the summit?

08:41.229 --> 08:42.521
- Not officially, no.

08:42.605 --> 08:43.564
Miss Khin is considered

08:43.648 --> 08:44.774
a political dissident

08:44.857 --> 08:46.192
and enemy combatant

08:46.275 --> 08:47.568
of the recognized government
of Kalpoor,

08:47.652 --> 08:49.153
which is why my office

08:49.237 --> 08:52.240
cannot be involved
with what I need you to do.

08:52.323 --> 08:54.325
- But all due respect,
Prime Minister,

08:54.408 --> 08:55.660
I'm not in the business

08:55.743 --> 08:57.245
of eliminating
political dissidents.

08:57.328 --> 08:58.829
- Neither is
the British government.

08:58.913 --> 09:00.623
Miss Khin is here
to speak with the president

09:00.706 --> 09:03.417
of Kalpoor in hopes
a truce can be arranged.

09:03.501 --> 09:06.712
I need somebody
outside official channels

09:06.796 --> 09:08.923
to look after her
during her stay.

09:09.006 --> 09:10.758
- Happy to help.

09:10.841 --> 09:12.885
Foreign diplomats is extra,
of course.

09:12.969 --> 09:14.095
- Of course.

09:16.180 --> 09:19.308
- My father was
a man of the people.

09:19.392 --> 09:22.603
And the people of Kalpoor have
been abandoned by a government

09:22.687 --> 09:25.106
that claims independence
whilst allowing the yoke

09:25.189 --> 09:27.984
of British colonialism
to remain around our necks

09:28.067 --> 09:29.527
in order to line
their own pockets.

09:29.610 --> 09:31.445
- I see we're off
to a passionate start.

09:31.529 --> 09:32.655
- Prime Minister.

09:32.738 --> 09:33.948
These talks
are a waste of time,

09:34.031 --> 09:35.616
as I told you they would be.

09:35.700 --> 09:37.910
Miss Khin's only goal
is to destabilize my country...

09:37.994 --> 09:40.955
- It's not your country.
- And overthrow my government.

09:41.038 --> 09:42.915
This meeting is over.

09:42.999 --> 09:45.751
She's no different
than her father.

09:45.835 --> 09:49.005
- Thank you, Mr. President.
Such a lovely compliment.

09:49.088 --> 09:51.257
[diplomats murmuring]

09:53.718 --> 09:55.177
- I thought we were here
to find

09:55.261 --> 09:56.846
common ground, Miss Khin.

09:56.929 --> 09:58.347
- Oh, one doesn't find
common ground

09:58.431 --> 09:59.849
with a python, Prime Minister.

09:59.932 --> 10:01.392
Only a lack of air.

10:02.101 --> 10:04.270
- May I introduce
Mr. Alfred Pennyworth,

10:04.353 --> 10:07.148
a private security consultant
I thought could act

10:07.231 --> 10:09.817
as a guide
while you're in London.

10:09.900 --> 10:11.527
- Pleased to meet you, madam.

10:11.610 --> 10:13.237
- Do I look like
I'm here to see Big Ben

10:13.321 --> 10:15.072
and Trafalgar Square?
- You should.

10:15.156 --> 10:16.991
The fountains
and the bronze reliefs

10:17.074 --> 10:18.159
were made from French cannon.

10:18.242 --> 10:19.827
They're... quite beautiful.

10:19.910 --> 10:22.371
- Prime Minister.
- While on British soil,

10:22.455 --> 10:24.623
your safety
is my responsibility.

10:24.707 --> 10:27.960
- Her safety is
my responsibility, sir.

10:28.044 --> 10:32.590
And I don't need help from
a British security consultant

10:32.673 --> 10:35.217
who is, no doubt,
reporting back to you.

10:35.301 --> 10:37.219
- Mr. Win is right.

10:37.303 --> 10:38.971
If you want
someone to spy on me,

10:39.055 --> 10:41.515
you're gonna have
to try harder than that.

10:46.979 --> 10:48.522
- Well I guess
that's that, then.

10:48.606 --> 10:50.775
- Miss Khin's views
on the matter are irrelevant.

10:50.858 --> 10:52.026
Follow her.

10:52.109 --> 10:53.694
- Spy on her?
- Watch out for her.

10:53.778 --> 10:55.863
The eyes of the world are on us
during the summit,

10:55.946 --> 10:58.574
and I can't have any surprises.

10:58.657 --> 11:00.201
Any questions?

11:00.284 --> 11:03.120
- Protection is one price.
Spying's extra.

11:04.538 --> 11:05.873
- Of course.

11:06.791 --> 11:09.710
[uneasy music]

11:09.794 --> 11:14.548
♪ ♪

11:14.632 --> 11:15.966
[doorbell ringing]

11:16.050 --> 11:17.593
- I'll get it.

11:17.676 --> 11:20.262
- Thanks, Gladys.

11:21.555 --> 11:23.766
[door creaks open]
- Oh, hello.

11:23.849 --> 11:25.101
- Hello.

11:25.184 --> 11:26.602
Guess who's back.

11:26.685 --> 11:28.562
[slow jazz music]

11:28.646 --> 11:30.898
- Ah, Patricia.
- Thomas.

11:30.981 --> 11:33.234
- Hi.

11:33.317 --> 11:36.112
- Hello, Martha.
- Hi.

11:36.195 --> 11:38.239
When did you get into town?

11:38.322 --> 11:40.074
- Just now,
I would have called,

11:40.157 --> 11:42.451
but thought I'd surprise you.

11:42.535 --> 11:46.455
- Yeah, uh.
It worked!

11:46.539 --> 11:47.873
- How are you guys?

11:47.957 --> 11:49.458
It feels
like it's been forever.

11:49.542 --> 11:52.628
- We're good, yeah.
Thomas?

11:52.711 --> 11:56.090
- Yeah.
Yes, we are.

11:56.173 --> 11:57.508
We're good!

11:57.591 --> 12:00.344
What are you doing here?
Uh--in London, I mean.

12:00.428 --> 12:03.931
- I am in town for the new
Francis Fuchs art installation.

12:04.014 --> 12:05.433
- Oh.

12:05.516 --> 12:06.809
- Lovely.

12:06.892 --> 12:07.977
- You have no idea

12:08.060 --> 12:09.270
who Francis Fuchs is, do you?

12:09.353 --> 12:10.646
Of course you don't.

12:10.729 --> 12:12.606
You have busy lives
and a daughter to raise.

12:12.690 --> 12:14.275
Where is my niece, anyhow?

12:14.358 --> 12:15.568
I brought her a great present.

12:15.651 --> 12:18.612
Her ears are pierced, right?
- Oh, no.

12:18.696 --> 12:20.573
- Oh. Well,
I could pierce them for her.

12:20.656 --> 12:22.950
- Oh, no, no, no.

12:25.119 --> 12:28.330
- So, um...
where are you staying?

12:28.414 --> 12:30.624
- Well, here, of course.
Where else?

12:30.708 --> 12:32.501
- Hm.
- [chuckles]

12:34.378 --> 12:36.213
- I have to admit,
I was somewhat surprised

12:36.297 --> 12:38.090
you called me, Mary.

12:38.174 --> 12:41.218
- Well, you didn't leave me
much choice.

12:41.302 --> 12:44.972
I waited for a month,
and when you didn't ring,

12:45.055 --> 12:47.725
I thought you must have been
scared off.

12:47.808 --> 12:49.894
- I was a little worried.
I'm sorry.

12:49.977 --> 12:51.187
- Don't be.

12:51.270 --> 12:55.191
It's why I wanted
to talk to you today.

12:55.274 --> 12:57.026
Try and explain things.

12:57.109 --> 12:58.903
- I appreciate that.

12:58.986 --> 13:00.654
While I'm sure
there's an explanation

13:00.738 --> 13:03.908
for most of what I saw,
I just don't know

13:03.991 --> 13:06.076
if I'm the kind of chap
you're looking for.

13:10.289 --> 13:12.958
- Are you sure we don't have
that the wrong way around?

13:13.042 --> 13:14.919
- Just think we might be
chalk and cheese.

13:15.002 --> 13:15.920
- Maybe we are.

13:16.003 --> 13:17.588
Maybe we aren't.

13:17.671 --> 13:20.508
Life's short.
Why not find out?

13:25.846 --> 13:29.016
Anyway, if you don't think
it's worth giving it a go,

13:29.099 --> 13:32.853
no harm done, and I wish
you the best of luck.

13:32.937 --> 13:35.606
- Wait.

13:35.689 --> 13:38.526
Don't go.

13:38.609 --> 13:40.778
Maybe you're right.

13:40.861 --> 13:42.071
Maybe.

13:42.154 --> 13:43.697
- Well,
be still my beating heart.

13:43.781 --> 13:47.368
- I'd love to keep talking
with you, Mary.

13:47.451 --> 13:49.703
If that's all right?

13:49.787 --> 13:51.705
- Yeah.

13:51.789 --> 13:54.750
[warm music]

13:54.833 --> 14:01.924
♪ ♪

14:02.758 --> 14:04.552
- Boy, pay attention.

14:04.635 --> 14:07.012
- Sorry.

14:07.096 --> 14:08.597
- Since when do you read books?

14:08.681 --> 14:12.184
- Sally gave it to me.
It's about art.

14:12.268 --> 14:15.062
- Good, is it?
- I couldn't tell you.

14:15.145 --> 14:17.398
Can't understand much.

14:17.481 --> 14:18.899
- So why you reading it, then?

14:18.983 --> 14:20.859
- I'm thinking she's
gonna be asking questions.

14:20.943 --> 14:22.278
- What, she gives you homework?

14:22.361 --> 14:24.113
- Ha-ha.

14:27.491 --> 14:30.452
[intriguing music]

14:30.536 --> 14:37.626
♪ ♪

14:58.897 --> 15:00.065
- Hang about.

15:00.149 --> 15:02.318
[dramatic music]

15:03.694 --> 15:05.237
- Get down!

15:05.321 --> 15:07.781
Arjun!

15:07.865 --> 15:09.116
Arjun!

15:09.199 --> 15:10.618
Take cover!

15:10.701 --> 15:12.953
Fuck!

15:13.037 --> 15:14.121
It's all right.
Look at me.

15:14.204 --> 15:15.581
- She's got guts.

15:15.664 --> 15:17.249
- I'll grab her
and meet you back at the pub.

15:17.333 --> 15:19.460
- Stay with me!

15:19.543 --> 15:20.919
It's okay.

15:21.003 --> 15:22.671
♪ ♪

15:22.755 --> 15:23.756
- He's gone.

15:23.839 --> 15:26.008
Well, come on, then.
Come on.

15:27.301 --> 15:28.719
Let's go.

15:28.802 --> 15:35.893
♪ ♪

15:40.147 --> 15:41.815
- How long has it been

15:41.899 --> 15:44.401
since you've had
a good night's sleep?

15:44.485 --> 15:47.446
- Babies are right nuisances,
aren't they?

15:47.529 --> 15:49.406
- Yes.

15:49.490 --> 15:52.534
- Why won't you tell us
where Salt is?

15:52.618 --> 15:55.412
- Because he's not worth
the trouble or the danger.

15:55.496 --> 15:57.081
- That's my business.
What do you care?

15:57.164 --> 15:58.874
- I care about you, Bet.

15:58.957 --> 16:01.418
You saved my life,
and in a dispassionate,

16:01.502 --> 16:03.879
Christian sort of way,
one might say I love you.

16:03.962 --> 16:05.506
- Get out.
- I don't want to see you

16:05.589 --> 16:07.299
get hurt.

16:07.383 --> 16:10.052
- Well, that's very nice,
I'm sure, but I'll not stop

16:10.135 --> 16:11.929
just because you've got
a soft spot for us.

16:12.012 --> 16:14.848
I'll keep looking
for Salt no matter what.

16:14.932 --> 16:16.934
You could save us a lot
of bother, though.

16:17.017 --> 16:18.644
That's all.

16:18.727 --> 16:20.396
- I'll tell you what.

16:20.479 --> 16:23.232
I'll give you John Salt

16:23.315 --> 16:25.025
if you give me Julie.

16:25.109 --> 16:27.152
- What?
- Salt for Julie.

16:27.236 --> 16:31.365
You cannot take her around,
killing people willy-nilly.

16:31.448 --> 16:33.575
What sort
of upbringing is that?

16:33.659 --> 16:37.204
I can give her a good
and safe home, and you?

16:37.287 --> 16:40.582
Well, you can have
your vengeance.

16:40.666 --> 16:42.000
Why not?

16:42.084 --> 16:43.794
You said yourself
she's a right nuisance.

16:43.877 --> 16:45.546
- She's a fucking nightmare,
but--

16:45.629 --> 16:46.964
- But?
- No.

16:47.047 --> 16:48.215
No, I won't give her up.

16:48.298 --> 16:50.050
- Why not?
You know it makes sense.

16:50.134 --> 16:52.010
- Because.
That's why, because.

16:52.094 --> 16:53.220
- Because you love her.

16:54.138 --> 16:55.973
And you can see
a future for yourself

16:56.056 --> 16:59.059
as her mother,
more important than vengeance,

16:59.143 --> 17:02.646
better than hatred
and bloodlust.

17:02.730 --> 17:04.857
[soft twangy music]

17:04.940 --> 17:07.067
- All right.

17:07.151 --> 17:09.903
I admit it.

17:09.987 --> 17:13.073
I love her.

17:13.157 --> 17:15.117
But that's not
why I'm keeping her.

17:15.200 --> 17:18.203
I won't give her up
because I'm stubborn,

17:18.287 --> 17:20.456
and I won't let
the likes of you

17:20.539 --> 17:22.541
tell me right from wrong.

17:22.624 --> 17:24.501
You wouldn't know
the first thing

17:24.585 --> 17:27.379
about hatred and bloodlust.

17:27.463 --> 17:29.214
I know.

17:29.298 --> 17:30.716
I know in here.

17:30.799 --> 17:33.218
- Bet, my dear--
- I am what I am.

17:33.302 --> 17:37.097
And I'll keep Julie,
and I'll keep spilling blood

17:37.181 --> 17:40.934
until I find Salt and kill him.

17:43.353 --> 17:44.855
And that's that.

17:47.357 --> 17:49.276
Thanks for the tea.

17:49.359 --> 17:50.611
- Wait.

17:50.694 --> 17:52.112
Wait, wait, wait.

17:54.948 --> 17:57.910
[pen clatters]

17:57.993 --> 17:59.369
Here.

17:59.453 --> 18:01.455
- What's this?
- A lesser of two evils.

18:01.538 --> 18:03.916
- Eh?
- Salt's whereabouts.

18:03.999 --> 18:06.126
- I can't make
head nor tail of it.

18:06.210 --> 18:09.254
You call that writing?

18:13.050 --> 18:14.635
- Here you are.

18:15.385 --> 18:19.097
- You're all right, Mrs. G.
- Now, be very careful.

18:19.181 --> 18:21.558
And let this be
the last one, please.

18:21.642 --> 18:23.393
No more bloodshed.

18:24.895 --> 18:26.522
- Promise.

18:30.400 --> 18:32.945
- Hear that, Julie?
Job on.

18:40.118 --> 18:45.666
- All right, come on.

18:45.749 --> 18:47.376
This way.

18:52.089 --> 18:53.841
Right.

18:53.924 --> 18:55.217
How are you, then, okay?

18:55.300 --> 18:56.593
- I'm fine.
It's not the first time

18:56.677 --> 18:57.845
a government has tried
to kill me.

18:57.928 --> 18:59.388
- How do you know it was them?

18:59.471 --> 19:01.390
- It's neither mine nor yours,
not that it matters.

19:01.473 --> 19:02.850
I need to go to my hotel.

19:02.933 --> 19:04.268
- No, that's not a good idea.

19:04.351 --> 19:06.353
Those men knew
where you were going to be.

19:06.436 --> 19:08.522
Someone's giving them
your private schedule.

19:08.605 --> 19:10.065
Now, come on.
- If you're not taking me

19:10.148 --> 19:12.943
to my hotel,
where are you taking me?

19:13.026 --> 19:14.987
- Well, there's
strong public support

19:15.070 --> 19:16.738
for isolating the PWEs

19:16.822 --> 19:20.450
from the general population
as a protective measure,

19:20.534 --> 19:23.537
to ensure their safety,
and ours.

19:23.620 --> 19:25.372
Well, let's get
some reaction from...

19:25.455 --> 19:28.292
[door clatters open]

19:28.375 --> 19:29.668
- A public house?

19:31.461 --> 19:33.964
This is your safe place?
- Trust me.

19:34.047 --> 19:37.217
This particular pub is one
of the safest places in London.

19:37.301 --> 19:38.969
This way.

19:48.645 --> 19:50.856
- Zahra Khin, Mr. Chadley,

19:50.939 --> 19:53.066
one of my associates.

19:53.150 --> 19:55.027
- A pleasure, madam.
- Call whoever you need.

19:55.110 --> 19:56.737
Just don't tell anyone
you're here.

19:56.820 --> 19:58.280
- Thank you.

19:58.363 --> 19:59.781
Privacy, please.

20:02.034 --> 20:04.912
- The PM's office
is ringing every ten minutes,

20:04.995 --> 20:07.539
asking for you.

20:07.623 --> 20:08.957
Who's the lady?

20:09.041 --> 20:11.043
- Rebel leader, sort of thing.

20:11.126 --> 20:12.794
In town for the summit.

20:12.878 --> 20:15.380
[mysterious music]

20:15.464 --> 20:17.841
- Take special care.
- Eh?

20:17.925 --> 20:21.261
- Special care.
- What do you mean?

20:21.345 --> 20:23.430
- She's trouble.

20:23.513 --> 20:24.681
- Isn't she, though?

20:24.765 --> 20:27.809
♪ ♪

20:27.893 --> 20:29.728
- So...

20:29.811 --> 20:31.104
how long do you think
you'll be staying with us?

20:31.188 --> 20:32.731
- I don't know.
Why?

20:32.814 --> 20:34.358
- No reason.
Just, um...

20:34.441 --> 20:37.486
Well, with--what with work
and Samantha,

20:37.569 --> 20:39.571
things can get
a little hectic around here.

20:39.655 --> 20:41.198
- You don't want me
to stay with you?

20:41.281 --> 20:42.491
- No.

20:42.574 --> 20:43.992
It's not that
we don't want you to stay.

20:44.076 --> 20:45.494
- Yeah.
We just--we just know

20:45.577 --> 20:48.080
that you value your own space.

20:48.163 --> 20:49.623
- What's going on?

20:49.706 --> 20:51.375
Are you guys' fighting?
- No.

20:51.458 --> 20:52.793
Why would you say that?

20:52.876 --> 20:54.336
- Yeah, we're not fighting,

20:54.419 --> 20:55.754
and even if we were,
it'd be none of your concern.

20:55.837 --> 20:57.089
- Whatever.

20:57.172 --> 20:58.173
Dad said you were
acting weird,

20:58.256 --> 20:59.216
and he was right.

20:59.299 --> 21:00.634
- Weird?

21:00.717 --> 21:02.427
Dad said I was acting weird?

21:02.511 --> 21:03.887
- Something like that.

21:03.971 --> 21:05.597
You know I don't listen
very closely to him.

21:05.681 --> 21:06.974
- Son of a bitch.

21:07.057 --> 21:10.185
- Why?
Did he do something wrong?

21:11.937 --> 21:13.981
What?

21:14.064 --> 21:15.649
Did he not give you
enough hugs?

21:15.732 --> 21:17.442
You've always been so sensitive
when it comes to that.

21:17.526 --> 21:18.652
- Okay, drop it.

21:18.735 --> 21:20.320
- Well, at least he made
the effort

21:20.404 --> 21:21.738
flying over here to see you.

21:21.822 --> 21:23.365
He barely acknowledges
that I'm alive.

21:23.448 --> 21:24.992
- You want
to know what happened?

21:25.075 --> 21:26.493
What he did?

21:26.576 --> 21:28.662
I'll tell--
- Thomas.

21:28.745 --> 21:31.331
- He gave me an experimental
mind control drug

21:31.415 --> 21:33.083
that he developed with the CIA

21:33.166 --> 21:36.169
so that I would kill Martha
in order to save his skin.

21:36.253 --> 21:38.255
- Whoa!
Okay, that's not cool.

21:38.338 --> 21:41.258
- So please
don't mention him again.

21:41.341 --> 21:43.468
- You don't have to be
so melodramatic.

21:43.552 --> 21:45.804
- He tried to make me
kill my own wife!

21:45.887 --> 21:49.182
- But you didn't, did you?
She's sitting right there.

21:49.266 --> 21:51.268
All's well
that ends well, right?

21:51.351 --> 21:53.353
- I guess she has a point.

21:53.437 --> 21:56.023
- So you're a real doctor
now, huh?

21:56.106 --> 21:57.357
I'm so proud of you.

21:57.441 --> 21:59.526
You can write prescriptions?
Huh?

21:59.609 --> 22:01.194
- [sighs]

22:01.278 --> 22:03.697
- Seriously, can you?

22:05.824 --> 22:08.160
- The prime minister wants me
to escort you to Whitehall

22:08.243 --> 22:10.454
to discuss your
official protection detail.

22:10.537 --> 22:12.289
- Does he now?
- He does.

22:12.372 --> 22:14.041
For your safety.

22:14.124 --> 22:15.709
- This isn't about my safety.

22:15.792 --> 22:18.211
It's about bad press during
his precious little summit.

22:18.295 --> 22:21.214
- That don't change the fact
your life's in danger.

22:21.298 --> 22:22.674
- My life has been
in danger since the day

22:22.758 --> 22:24.384
I took over from my father.

22:24.468 --> 22:26.762
He gave
his life for his country.

22:26.845 --> 22:28.305
I'm willing to do the same.

22:28.388 --> 22:30.307
- Yeah, but willing and eager

22:30.390 --> 22:32.267
are two different things.

22:32.350 --> 22:33.643
Anyway, come on.
We should go.

22:33.727 --> 22:34.936
- I'm not going
to Whitehall

22:35.020 --> 22:36.480
until I find out
who the traitor is.

22:36.563 --> 22:38.273
- Well, how are you
planning on doing that?

22:38.356 --> 22:40.734
- Simple enough.
I told my people where I am.

22:40.817 --> 22:42.152
- I told you not to do that.

22:42.235 --> 22:44.237
- I know.
That's what gave me the idea.

22:44.321 --> 22:47.991
If there is a traitor,
they'll want to finish the job.

22:48.075 --> 22:49.409
- Yeah.
- So I've given them

22:49.493 --> 22:50.702
a chance to do that.

22:50.786 --> 22:52.662
We have the advantage.

22:52.746 --> 22:55.082
We know they're coming.
- We?

22:55.165 --> 22:56.792
- My head of security
will be here any minute.

22:56.875 --> 22:58.335
- Smashing.

23:05.592 --> 23:07.135
- Is Plumstead nice?

23:07.219 --> 23:09.721
- Our flat is...

23:09.805 --> 23:13.725
Sorry, my flat is
near the common.

23:13.809 --> 23:16.269
Good birdwatching.

23:16.353 --> 23:18.480
I still say
"our" and "we" a lot.

23:18.563 --> 23:21.316
I'm trying
to get better at that.

23:21.399 --> 23:23.819
- My Arthur's been gone
for five years,

23:23.902 --> 23:27.114
and I still find myself talking
to his photograph.

23:27.197 --> 23:29.616
I could barely get a word in
when we were married.

23:29.699 --> 23:32.577
Silver lining, I suppose.

23:32.661 --> 23:35.580
- When my wife ran off,

23:35.664 --> 23:37.124
I told myself
it was no one's fault,

23:37.207 --> 23:39.793
that we just weren't right
for each other.

23:39.876 --> 23:42.170
But the truth is,
she wanted more out of life,

23:42.254 --> 23:45.799
and for some reason, I didn't.

23:45.882 --> 23:48.635
But you know what?

23:48.718 --> 23:50.095
Now I do.

23:50.178 --> 23:53.098
I want more, Mary.

23:53.181 --> 23:55.225
Would you give me
another chance?

23:56.726 --> 24:00.188
- I'm not sure you're up
for an interesting life.

24:00.272 --> 24:03.108
- Try me.
I'll show you.

24:05.610 --> 24:07.070
- How's your dancing?

24:07.154 --> 24:10.157
[methodical waltz music]

24:10.240 --> 24:17.289
♪ ♪

24:23.753 --> 24:27.382
[laughs]

24:40.604 --> 24:42.314
[laughs]

24:42.397 --> 24:45.358
[suspenseful music]

24:45.442 --> 24:48.403
♪ ♪

24:48.486 --> 24:49.738
- Where's Zahra Khin?!

24:49.821 --> 24:51.156
Bring her out,
or we start shooting!

24:51.239 --> 24:53.200
- All this fuss
and only two of you?

24:53.283 --> 24:55.035
- I'm not fucking about!
- I'm afraid you are.

24:55.118 --> 24:58.413
- Drop your guns and take off
those fucking masks.

24:58.496 --> 25:03.001
♪ ♪

25:08.381 --> 25:10.217
- Hey, Alfie.

25:10.300 --> 25:13.053
- Fuck's sake. Gary.

25:13.136 --> 25:15.555
You know this is my pub?
- Sorry, Alfie.

25:15.639 --> 25:17.224
It's just a job.
You know it goes.

25:17.307 --> 25:20.227
- Yeah.
How's your mum?

25:20.310 --> 25:21.436
- Not bad.

25:21.519 --> 25:24.856
Her arthritis
has been acting up.

25:24.940 --> 25:26.733
You gonna kill us?

25:26.816 --> 25:28.068
- Nah.

25:28.151 --> 25:29.402
We'll have a pint,
see what you can tell us.

25:29.486 --> 25:31.947
- No.
These men need to die.

25:32.030 --> 25:33.406
- Easy, mate, lower your gun.

25:33.490 --> 25:35.075
- I don't take orders from you.

25:35.158 --> 25:37.744
- All right, Miss Khin,
please tell your man

25:37.827 --> 25:39.287
to lower his weapon.

25:39.371 --> 25:41.414
- My driver's dead
because of them.

25:41.498 --> 25:43.375
He had children, a family.

25:43.458 --> 25:45.043
- Yeah, look,
I understand, but this is

25:45.126 --> 25:47.295
my bar, so I make the rules.

25:47.379 --> 25:48.880
- So they just
get away with it?

25:48.964 --> 25:50.090
- No.

25:50.173 --> 25:51.341
But they might be able
to tell us

25:51.424 --> 25:53.343
who betrayed you.

25:53.426 --> 25:55.470
- I already know.

25:55.553 --> 25:57.472
I knew the minute
they showed up.

26:01.184 --> 26:04.271
I am so disappointed
in you, Win.

26:04.354 --> 26:05.855
- What?

26:05.939 --> 26:07.440
No!
These people

26:07.524 --> 26:10.402
have been filling
your head with lies.

26:10.485 --> 26:12.362
I will kill them all
where they stand.

26:12.445 --> 26:14.447
- Stop!

26:14.531 --> 26:17.617
You were the only person
I gave this location to.

26:20.036 --> 26:21.788
I didn't want to believe it.

26:23.748 --> 26:27.127
But somehow I just knew.

26:27.210 --> 26:28.670
Why did you do this?

26:30.005 --> 26:34.384
How could you betray
what we believed in?

26:34.467 --> 26:37.012
What my father believed in?

26:39.097 --> 26:40.765
Answer me!

26:40.849 --> 26:45.520
- Because I can't feed
my family with belief.

26:45.603 --> 26:50.567
It has been ten years,
and nothing has changed.

26:50.650 --> 26:53.153
They deserve more from me.

26:54.904 --> 26:56.698
- So did I.

27:00.952 --> 27:02.746
Who put you up to this?

27:02.829 --> 27:04.914
- [inhales]

27:04.998 --> 27:06.333
[pounding on door]

27:06.416 --> 27:08.835
- I said I was not
to be disturbed!

27:08.918 --> 27:09.878
[dramatic music]

27:09.961 --> 27:12.589
- [grunting]

27:12.672 --> 27:19.637
♪ ♪

27:21.056 --> 27:22.682
- Oh, my God.

27:22.766 --> 27:27.145
You were a prisoner
in the Tower of London?

27:27.228 --> 27:28.605
That's crazy.

27:29.856 --> 27:31.524
- Yes, it is.

27:31.608 --> 27:33.526
- Okay.

27:33.610 --> 27:37.572
I guess Dad is, like,
totally beyond not cool.

27:37.655 --> 27:41.368
No wonder you're mad at him.
So what are you gonna do?

27:43.286 --> 27:44.913
- What can I do?

27:44.996 --> 27:48.333
- I don't know.
You're asking my advice?

27:48.416 --> 27:50.043
You're the smart one.

27:50.126 --> 27:51.628
- Right.

27:51.711 --> 27:55.256
- That's me.

27:55.340 --> 27:57.842
I've allowed this thing
to tear my family apart.

28:01.012 --> 28:03.348
What kind of a man

28:03.431 --> 28:05.225
lets his own father do this

28:05.308 --> 28:06.684
without any consequences?

28:06.768 --> 28:09.396
- You, apparently.

28:09.479 --> 28:12.690
- Rhetorical question, Pat,
but thanks.

28:15.485 --> 28:17.654
- I'm here for you, brother.

28:22.242 --> 28:23.743
- I don't know what to do, Pat.

28:27.789 --> 28:29.332
I don't know.

28:31.292 --> 28:32.502
[car honks]

28:32.585 --> 28:35.922
- Oh, well.
There's my ride.

28:36.005 --> 28:38.925
I'm sure you'll figure it out.

28:39.008 --> 28:40.301
You always do.

28:45.682 --> 28:47.267
[door closes]

28:47.350 --> 28:50.270
[moody music]

28:50.353 --> 28:57.444
♪ ♪

28:58.862 --> 29:01.531
- I thought you said
this was a new art exhibit.

29:01.614 --> 29:02.991
- It is.

29:04.325 --> 29:05.869
- Where the fuck's the art?

29:09.205 --> 29:10.707
- Here he is.

29:14.127 --> 29:17.172
[experimental music]

29:20.049 --> 29:23.470
- My friends.

29:23.553 --> 29:26.389
We live
in the moment of history

29:26.473 --> 29:29.350
in which the commodity of art

29:29.434 --> 29:31.144
threatens to complete

29:31.227 --> 29:35.148
its colonization
of social life,

29:35.231 --> 29:37.984
in which we have gone
from being

29:38.067 --> 29:44.908
into having, and having
into merely appearing,

29:44.991 --> 29:50.497
until we become
the commodity itself.

29:52.248 --> 29:58.838
Which is why,
I tonight--I give you not art,

29:58.922 --> 30:02.217
not simulation,

30:02.300 --> 30:08.223
not a representation
of reality,

30:08.306 --> 30:11.017
but reality itself.

30:12.810 --> 30:14.979
[groaning]

30:17.649 --> 30:19.192
And wet.

30:24.030 --> 30:25.448
[crowd gasps]

30:29.035 --> 30:31.996
[soft tense music]

30:32.080 --> 30:34.457
♪ ♪

30:34.541 --> 30:35.875
- Wait here.

30:35.959 --> 30:43.049
♪ ♪

30:58.773 --> 31:01.025
Clear.

31:01.109 --> 31:04.028
I've posted men on the corners
and the entrances.

31:06.406 --> 31:07.574
You keep these closed.

31:12.495 --> 31:15.498
I'll be in the lobby
if you need anything.

31:15.582 --> 31:18.209
- I'm sure I'll be fine.

31:18.293 --> 31:20.503
No reason for you to spend
all night in the lobby.

31:20.587 --> 31:23.923
- Just a precaution.
No plans, anyhow.

31:25.008 --> 31:27.302
- I'm gonna drink now.

31:30.221 --> 31:31.931
Perhaps you care to join?

31:34.183 --> 31:35.810
- Thank you, miss.

31:37.353 --> 31:38.896
Rules are simple.

31:38.980 --> 31:42.317
Every card in the deck
has a pair, except for one,

31:42.400 --> 31:44.986
the dirty queen,
which is cursed.

31:45.069 --> 31:47.447
- [snickers]
I know how she feels.

31:47.530 --> 31:49.365
- We take her out
of the deck and then deal

31:49.449 --> 31:52.118
the rest of the cards.

31:52.201 --> 31:54.120
Then discard any pairs
you have, and the cards

31:54.203 --> 31:56.539
you have left is your hand.

31:56.623 --> 31:59.125
- Okay.
And then?

31:59.208 --> 32:01.336
- Then we start drawing
from each other's hands,

32:01.419 --> 32:04.339
and whoever's left
with the dirty queen loses.

32:05.548 --> 32:07.634
- I think I can follow that.

32:14.015 --> 32:17.060
Thanks for sticking around.

32:17.143 --> 32:19.020
- Want to make sure
there's no blowback

32:19.103 --> 32:20.229
from the care package
we dropped off

32:20.313 --> 32:23.149
at your president's hotel.

32:23.232 --> 32:24.942
- Yeah.

32:30.406 --> 32:32.575
- I know that kind
of betrayal is tough,

32:32.659 --> 32:35.912
but you shouldn't let it
get to you.

32:35.995 --> 32:38.790
- Shouldn't I?

32:38.873 --> 32:42.960
- Everyone has a price.
It's the way of the world.

32:43.044 --> 32:44.420
- [scoffs]

32:44.504 --> 32:46.839
I don't have a price.

32:46.923 --> 32:49.050
My father didn't have a price.

32:49.133 --> 32:52.345
Just because men
like Win and you do

32:52.428 --> 32:54.097
doesn't make it right.

32:55.807 --> 32:58.518
- I charge for my services,

32:58.601 --> 33:00.937
but my honor isn't for sale.

33:01.020 --> 33:03.564
For rent, maybe,
but not for sale.

33:07.151 --> 33:10.405
- You said
everyone's got a price.

33:10.488 --> 33:12.073
Maybe no one's found yours yet.

33:12.156 --> 33:13.533
- Possibly.

33:13.616 --> 33:16.369
It's over a million quid,
anyhow.

33:16.452 --> 33:19.872
- Oh yeah?
How's that?

33:19.956 --> 33:21.541
- Someone offered me
a million quid

33:21.624 --> 33:24.001
to do something naughty,
and I walked away.

33:25.336 --> 33:29.090
- You walked away
from a million pounds?

33:29.173 --> 33:30.383
- Yeah.

33:30.466 --> 33:32.802
Can we change the subject?

33:41.978 --> 33:43.730
- What did they want you to do?

33:43.813 --> 33:47.275
- Break someone out of prison,
which I did,

33:47.358 --> 33:49.318
and put them on a plane,

33:49.402 --> 33:51.070
which I didn't.

33:51.154 --> 33:52.655
- Why not?

33:52.739 --> 33:54.657
- They didn't want to go.

33:54.741 --> 33:55.825
- That's it?

33:57.827 --> 34:00.747
- Most decisions
aren't complicated.

34:02.165 --> 34:05.001
Just comes down
to what you can live with.

34:06.627 --> 34:09.005
Who you want to see
when you look in the mirror.

34:11.632 --> 34:13.217
- And what do you see?

34:13.301 --> 34:16.012
[soft dramatic music]

34:16.095 --> 34:18.765
♪ ♪

34:18.848 --> 34:21.809
- An idiot who walked away
from a million quid.

34:22.935 --> 34:29.859
♪ ♪

34:43.247 --> 34:45.458
- What did you think
of the show?

34:45.541 --> 34:47.877
- I think I'm covered
in paint.

34:47.960 --> 34:49.253
- I'm serious.

34:49.337 --> 34:51.798
- So am I.
This was an expensive jacket.

34:51.881 --> 34:54.342
Fuck.
Wanted to chin the man.

34:54.425 --> 34:56.719
- You don't understand
social commentary.

34:56.803 --> 34:59.138
- Obviously, I don't, no.

34:59.222 --> 35:02.475
- I care about this stuff,
Dave Boy.

35:02.558 --> 35:04.310
I want you
to care about it as well.

35:04.393 --> 35:08.940
- Well, I'm here, aren't I?
I'm trying.

35:09.023 --> 35:12.276
- What if there was
something you could take

35:12.360 --> 35:14.612
to expand your mind,

35:14.695 --> 35:18.866
get in touch
with your inner artist?

35:18.950 --> 35:20.284
- I've seen
all the hippies

35:20.368 --> 35:22.286
dancing about on LSD.

35:22.370 --> 35:23.704
I don't think that's for me.

35:23.788 --> 35:25.081
- This is something new.

35:25.164 --> 35:26.666
Francis told me about it.

35:26.749 --> 35:28.584
It connects people
in a profound

35:28.668 --> 35:33.089
and spiritual level,
like sharing a dream.

35:33.172 --> 35:36.843
- Last dream I had,
I was naked as a baby,

35:36.926 --> 35:38.511
driving a double-decker bus

35:38.594 --> 35:40.596
'round and 'round
Trafalgar Square.

35:42.557 --> 35:43.850
- What do you say?

35:45.601 --> 35:49.188
You wanna share
a dream with me tonight?

35:55.695 --> 35:57.029
- Fuck it.

35:58.239 --> 35:59.782
Why not?

35:59.866 --> 36:01.409
Cheers.

36:05.079 --> 36:06.873
- [gasps] Good Lord.

36:06.956 --> 36:09.876
- Forgive me, Doctor.
I couldn't resist.

36:09.959 --> 36:13.045
You looked
so delightfully nervous.

36:13.129 --> 36:16.966
- Mr. Fuchs, I would never
have agreed to help you

36:17.049 --> 36:18.551
if I'd known it was
your intention

36:18.634 --> 36:20.177
to use Lullaby
in this manner.

36:20.261 --> 36:22.054
- And what manner is that?

36:23.097 --> 36:27.560
- Lullaby was designed
as a mind control drug,

36:27.643 --> 36:30.021
to strip away
an individual's defenses

36:30.104 --> 36:32.523
and provide a blank canvas,

36:32.607 --> 36:35.443
but we have to then give
a structure,

36:35.526 --> 36:36.569
a blueprint.

36:36.652 --> 36:37.570
- Or what?

36:37.653 --> 36:39.363
- That's just it.
Who knows

36:39.447 --> 36:41.949
what a completely unfettered
psyche

36:42.033 --> 36:43.743
might dream up on its own?

36:43.826 --> 36:45.077
Could be anything.

36:45.161 --> 36:47.079
- Yes, and isn't
that wonderful?

36:47.163 --> 36:48.247
- But--

36:48.331 --> 36:49.957
- You see a blank canvas,
Doctor,

36:50.041 --> 36:52.084
and think anarchy.

36:52.168 --> 36:56.172
I see one and think freedom.

36:56.255 --> 36:58.424
- How many did you give it to?

36:58.507 --> 37:00.092
- Just a small dose

37:00.176 --> 37:02.261
to a few special souls.

37:03.221 --> 37:04.931
Don't worry.

37:05.014 --> 37:08.017
This is only the beginning.

37:08.100 --> 37:10.019
- The beginning of what?

37:10.102 --> 37:12.939
And why the mask?

37:13.022 --> 37:15.149
What are you planning?

37:15.232 --> 37:17.276
- You'll see, Doctor.

37:17.360 --> 37:20.529
All in good time.

37:20.613 --> 37:22.323
You'll see.

37:22.406 --> 37:25.368
[eerie music]

37:25.451 --> 37:27.328
♪ ♪

37:29.413 --> 37:32.833
- Do you sleep
with all your female clients?

37:32.917 --> 37:34.627
- Well, word of mouth
plays a big part

37:34.710 --> 37:37.922
in attracting new clients,
so I like to do what I can.

37:38.005 --> 37:39.548
- Oh.

37:39.632 --> 37:41.384
Risky move.

37:41.467 --> 37:43.970
Could backfire.

37:44.053 --> 37:46.013
- Well, I never thought
of that.

37:50.142 --> 37:52.436
- [exhales]

38:00.194 --> 38:03.656
- Sorry about your driver.

38:03.739 --> 38:07.910
You did everything you could.

38:07.994 --> 38:11.831
- There was nothing to do.

38:11.914 --> 38:15.251
The bullet must have hit
his carotid artery

38:15.334 --> 38:17.336
for rapid blood loss like that.

38:17.420 --> 38:21.549
- You sound like a doctor.

38:21.632 --> 38:23.259
- I almost was one.

38:23.342 --> 38:26.721
I was in medical school when
my father was assassinated.

38:29.765 --> 38:33.310
Felt like my whole world ended
in that single moment.

38:33.394 --> 38:37.106
But I had to keep
his work going

38:37.189 --> 38:39.233
for the people of Kalpoor.

38:41.152 --> 38:44.697
For him.

38:44.780 --> 38:47.199
For me.

38:51.787 --> 38:53.164
What about you?

38:53.247 --> 38:54.707
- Me?

38:54.790 --> 38:58.461
I live with me mum.

38:58.544 --> 39:02.173
My dad passed away
five years ago.

39:02.256 --> 39:04.008
- Sorry.

39:04.091 --> 39:07.136
- You two would have gotten
along well, I imagine.

39:07.219 --> 39:08.429
- Why's that?

39:08.512 --> 39:10.181
- Shared interest.

39:13.768 --> 39:15.853
He tried to blow up
the queen and overthrow

39:15.936 --> 39:17.271
the government, for starters.

39:17.355 --> 39:18.856
- I remember reading
about an attack

39:18.939 --> 39:21.442
on the queen
before the civil war.

39:21.525 --> 39:22.985
That was your father?

39:23.069 --> 39:24.445
- He was a man
of his convictions,

39:24.528 --> 39:25.529
I'll give him that.

39:25.613 --> 39:26.906
I actually had to shoot him

39:26.989 --> 39:29.617
to try and stop it.

39:29.700 --> 39:31.118
- You shot your own dad?

39:31.202 --> 39:34.413
- I couldn't let
all those people die.

39:34.497 --> 39:35.956
- Is there
anyone you can trust?

39:36.040 --> 39:38.167
- I'd trust my best mate
with me life.

39:39.585 --> 39:40.961
You?

39:41.045 --> 39:43.589
- I haven't trusted anyone
since my Dad died.

39:49.470 --> 39:51.722
But I think
I can trust you, Alfie.

39:55.976 --> 39:58.104
I didn't come here
for the summit.

39:59.772 --> 40:01.607
- Well, what did
you come here for then?

40:01.690 --> 40:03.192
- To meet someone.

40:05.152 --> 40:08.197
A man who says
my father's still alive.

40:10.616 --> 40:12.576
- But you said
he was assassinated.

40:12.660 --> 40:14.453
- Because
that's what I was told.

40:14.537 --> 40:16.205
But we never recovered a body,
which means

40:16.288 --> 40:17.790
there is
a chance that he's alive.

40:17.873 --> 40:20.459
- Well, there's a better chance
it's a shakedown--

40:20.543 --> 40:21.961
or worse, a setup.

40:22.044 --> 40:23.295
- Yeah, I know.

40:23.379 --> 40:25.089
But it's my father
we're talking about.

40:26.507 --> 40:29.760
- Well,
what do they say happened?

40:29.844 --> 40:33.639
- That ten years ago,
he was kidnapped in Morocco.

40:33.722 --> 40:36.642
He was then taken overseas

40:36.725 --> 40:38.352
and has been locked up
in a secret location

40:38.435 --> 40:39.603
ever since.

40:40.729 --> 40:43.566
And this man?

40:43.649 --> 40:45.151
He knows where.

40:45.234 --> 40:48.154
[intense music]

40:48.237 --> 40:55.327
♪ ♪

41:02.084 --> 41:04.086
- [groaning]
- Jesus.

41:04.170 --> 41:06.505
- Oh, no, no, no, no, no.
That's twice.

41:06.589 --> 41:08.174
Dave Boy?

41:12.219 --> 41:14.180
You look like hell, mate.

41:14.263 --> 41:15.598
I'm pleased you're here,
as it goes.

41:15.681 --> 41:17.474
I need to talk
to you about somebody.

41:17.558 --> 41:19.602
- Sure, sure.

41:19.685 --> 41:22.646
[soft chiming music]

41:22.730 --> 41:23.689
♪ ♪

41:23.772 --> 41:25.149
- You don't look so good.

41:25.232 --> 41:26.692
Are you sure you're okay?

41:26.775 --> 41:29.695
- Oh, yeah.

41:29.778 --> 41:32.156
I don't really feel myself.

41:33.115 --> 41:36.660
But I'll be all right.

41:36.744 --> 41:40.080
What's... What's going on?

41:40.164 --> 41:43.751
- Do you remember a mission
we pulled about ten years ago?

41:43.834 --> 41:46.503
Kidnapped a political dissident
in Morocco?

41:46.587 --> 41:49.298
- Uh.
Not really, no, why?

41:49.381 --> 41:52.384
- I think the guy we grabbed
was Zahra's father.

41:52.468 --> 41:55.512
- Aye? That's...

41:55.596 --> 41:56.555
That's not good.

41:56.639 --> 41:57.556
- No.

41:57.640 --> 41:58.474
Not good.

41:58.557 --> 42:01.143
[soft jazz music]

42:01.227 --> 42:04.980
♪ ♪

42:09.318 --> 42:10.444
- [sniffs]

42:15.532 --> 42:18.452
[soft music]

42:18.535 --> 42:24.250
♪ ♪

42:24.333 --> 42:25.542
- Thomas?

42:32.091 --> 42:35.052
[intriguing music]

42:35.135 --> 42:42.226
♪ ♪

42:44.103 --> 42:46.397
[footsteps]

42:52.111 --> 42:53.779
- Mr. Wayne?
- Morning.

42:53.862 --> 42:55.406
- May I stow your bag?

42:55.489 --> 42:58.158
- I'll keep it with me, thanks.
- Of course, sir.

42:58.242 --> 43:02.079
We'll be landing in Gotham
at 8:00 a.m. local time.

43:02.162 --> 43:04.164
Welcome aboard.

43:04.248 --> 43:07.167
[dramatic music]

43:07.251 --> 43:08.711
♪ ♪

43:08.794 --> 43:11.130
- How about
a smile for Mr. Bear?

43:11.213 --> 43:13.799
You know he's your favorite.

43:13.882 --> 43:16.468
Come on.

43:19.763 --> 43:21.890
Well, well.

43:21.974 --> 43:24.184
And there he is.

43:24.268 --> 43:27.271
Mr. John Salt.

43:27.354 --> 43:30.607
You hold Mr. Bear.

43:30.691 --> 43:32.651
Mommy's got work to do.

43:32.735 --> 43:34.236
[stroller squeaks]

43:34.320 --> 43:41.410
♪ ♪

44:03.265 --> 44:05.059
- Bet Sykes.

44:05.142 --> 44:07.561
I thought that was you.

44:07.644 --> 44:09.980
- John Salt.

44:10.064 --> 44:12.316
I've been looking
for you for a long time.

44:12.399 --> 44:13.942
- And now you found me.

44:14.026 --> 44:16.028
May I ask how?

44:17.279 --> 44:20.866
- Ask away.
Fat lot of good it'll do you.

44:20.949 --> 44:22.451
- Well, I suppose
you found me

44:22.534 --> 44:25.412
through one of those Ravens
you tortured and killed.

44:25.496 --> 44:27.039
That was you, was it?

44:27.122 --> 44:28.707
- Guilty.

44:28.791 --> 44:30.042
Any last words?

44:30.125 --> 44:32.211
Not that there's
anyone around to hear them,

44:32.294 --> 44:34.254
or that I give a bloody damn.

44:34.338 --> 44:36.382
Hmm.

44:36.465 --> 44:41.261
This is for Lord Harwood.
A finer gentleman never lived.

44:41.345 --> 44:43.514
You weren't fit
to lick his boots.

44:43.597 --> 44:45.557
- Lord Harwood was
a weak-minded old fool

44:45.641 --> 44:46.767
who got what he deserved.

44:46.850 --> 44:48.060
- Right, you've had your say.

44:48.143 --> 44:50.187
- You should know

44:50.270 --> 44:51.647
I'm not the man I was.

44:51.730 --> 44:53.315
- Hmm, reformed are ya?

44:53.399 --> 44:54.441
- You could call it that.

44:54.525 --> 44:57.861
Remade, redeemed. Remodeled.

44:57.945 --> 44:59.071
- Bullocks.

44:59.154 --> 45:00.447
[gun fires]

45:02.699 --> 45:04.827
Good riddance to bad rubbish.

45:04.910 --> 45:07.621
[baby cries]

45:07.704 --> 45:09.873
Did the loud noise scare you?

45:09.957 --> 45:12.000
The bad man's gone now.

45:12.084 --> 45:14.044
There, there.

45:14.128 --> 45:17.047
[dramatic music]

45:17.131 --> 45:24.221
♪ ♪

45:25.305 --> 45:26.807
- Bloody hell.

45:26.890 --> 45:30.519
- I did warn you.

45:30.602 --> 45:32.980
I'm not the man I was.

45:33.063 --> 45:38.026
♪ ♪

45:40.154 --> 45:43.115
[adventurous music]

45:43.198 --> 45:50.289
♪ ♪
